dpress/?page_id=2',0,'page','',0),(4,1,'2015-04-02 09:15:49','2015-04-02 09:15:49','','Home page','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-v1','','','2015-04-02 09:15:49','2015-04-02 09:15:49','',2,'http://localhost/frank/?p=4',0,'revision','',0),(5,1,'2015-04-02 09:17:35','2015-04-02 09:17:35','<div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-61\" src=\"http://192.168.1.85/ladystoneviolins/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/silhouette-300x284.png\" alt=\"silhouette\" width=\"300\" height=\"284\" />\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h3>Hi, my name is Frank White and I\'ve been making and restoring violins for over 12 years.</h3>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n<img class=\"  wp-image-71 aligncenter\" src=\"http://192.168.1.85/ladystoneviolins/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Violin_VL100.png\" alt=\"Violin_VL100\" width=\"358\" height=\"130\" />\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div style=\"clear: both;\">\r\n<h3>My Story</h3>\r\nI am often asked what I did before I started making and restoring stringed instruments, and how I got the bug.\r\n\r\nSo I thought it best to clear that point up straight away.\r\n\r\nAfter starting work in 1955 as an apprentice plumber I spent the next 47 years connected in various ways with the building trade, particularly with building services and including twenty two years teaching.\r\n\r\nIn early 2001 whilst travelling to a job at Peggy Jackson’s in Scunthorpe, I heard Juliet Barker from Cambridge on the radio talking about her summer school violin making courses and that sounded very interesting. I was thinking about contacting her and mentioned it to Roy Gerrard (who was teaching me to play the violin at the time) and asked him if he had heard of her and her school. He said that he hadn’t heard of her, and added, ‘ what is wrong with Newark’?\r\n\r\nRoy explained about Newark School of Violin Making and suggested that we pay a visit on their Open day.\r\n\r\nWe did pay a visit, I was very impressed, and I enrolled on the part time evening course from September that year and by Christmas I had decided to apply for the full time course.\r\n\r\nIn 2002 I was offered a place on the 4 year course that started in September and included the foundation course.\r\n\r\nI took a year out between 2nd year and 3rd year of the main course to recover from operations on both hands and to try and prepare a little for 3rd year.\r\n\r\nAs it happens everything went well with the preparation and recovery and I completed the course in June 2007.\r\n\r\nDuring the course I made a six stringed Viola D’Amore,  two Violins, a Viola and a Cello.\r\n\r\nI was very fortunate in that I had two instruments played by the Allegri String Quartet in the evening concert of the Diploma Show.\r\n\r\nMy second violin (which I named Kay) was played by the 1st violinist in the 3rd movement of the Beethoven Opus 59 No3 Quartet.\r\n\r\nMy viola (which I named Susan) was played in the 4th movement in the Beethoven Opus 59 No3 Quartet.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\"><!-- free clip art from: http://www.clker.com/clipart-black-divider-no-background.html --><img src=\"http://www.clker.com/cliparts/L/N/U/m/A/J/black-divider-no-background-md.png\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"clear: both;\"><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"http://imageprocessor.websimages.com/width/300/crop/0,0,300x272/ladystoneviolins.webs.com/K-M-Q.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"272\" /></div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nThe Quartet of instruments that I made on the violin course have been on loan to the Kanneh Mason Quartet (a very talented foursome of siblings) since late summer 2012. I and my family get to hear them played on many occasions both as a quartet and in solo performances and for that we are very grateful.And for all this I would like to thank Peggy Jackson for calling me out at that time on that day - Juliet Barker for creating the spark, - Roy Gerrard for wafting the flame, -John Gosling and Narelle Freeman for all their help – All the staff and Students at the school, - Elizabeth my wife for her unwavering support all the way through, - and the Kanneh –Mason family for all the joy that they bring to us.\r\n\r\n</div>','About Frank','','publish','open','open','','about-us','','','2015-05-05 01:58:22','2015-05-05 01:58:22','',102,'http://localhost/frank/?page_id=5',1,'page','',0),(7,1,'2015-04-02 09:17:35','2015-04-02 09:17:35','','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','5-revision-v1','','','2015-04-02 09:17:35','2015-04-02 09:17:35','',5,'http://localhost/frank/?p=7',0,'revision','',0),(8,1,'2015-04-02 09:18:20','2015-04-02 09:18:20','','The Workshop','','trash','open','open','','the-workshop','','','2015-04-06 20:36:23','2015-04-06 20:36:23','',0,'http://localhost/frank/?page_id=8',3,'page','',0),(10,1,'2015-04-02 09:18:20','2015-04-02 09:18:20','','The workshop','','inherit','open','open','','8-revision-v1','','','2015-04-02 09:18:20','2015-04-02 09:18:20','',8,'http://localhost/frank/?p=10',0,'revision','',0),(11,1,'2015-04-02 09:18:32','2015-04-02 09:18:32','<div>\r\n\r\n<h3>\r\nI have experience working with Violins, Violas, Cellos and Violin d\'amores.\r\n\r\nI take on commissions, restoration and repair work, and also offer courses to pass on the skills I have gained over the past 12 years.\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\">\r\n<!-- free clip art from: http://www.clker.com/clipart-black-divider-no-background.html --><img src=\"http://www.clker.com/cliparts/L/N/U/m/A/J/black-divider-no-background-md.png\" alt=\"\" />\r\n</div>\r\n','Services','','publish','open','open','','courses-fees','','','2015-05-03 00:07:21','2015-05-03 00:07:21','',0,'http://localhost/frank/?page_id=11',2,'page','',0),(12,1,'2015-04-02 09:18:32','2015-04-02 09:18:32',' ','','','publish','open','open','','12','','','2015-05-05 01:59:38','2015-05-05 01:59:38','',0,'http://localhost/frank/?p=12',5,'nav_menu_item','',0),(13,1,'2015-04-02 